observations.recommendation:
In relation to this, we recommend the Honorable Mayor to:
1. Fast track the creation of an inventory committee of the municipality to conduct the physical count of its Road Network and prepare a report thereon (see Annex C);
2. Require the Municipal Accountant to update the local Road Network account based on the result of the physical count and disclose the said account on the Notes to Financial Statements (see Annex B);
3. Direct the General Services Officer to maintain a Local Road inventory and Road Map and prepare a report thereon at the end of every accounting period (See Annex A) as well as keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components (see Annex E).
4. Require the Municipal Engineer to provide the accountant and the General Services Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects.

In relation to this, we recommend the Honorable Mayor to:
a. Create an inventory committee of the municipality to conduct the physical count of its Road Network and prepare a report thereon (see Annex C);
b. Require the Municipal Accountant to update the local Road Network account based on the result of the physical count and disclose the said account on the Notes to Financial Statements (see Annex B);
c. Direct the General Services Officer to maintain a Local Road inventory and Road Map and prepare a report thereon at the end of every accounting period (See Annex A) as well as keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components (see Annex E);
d. Require the Municipal Engineer to provide the accountant and the General Services Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects.
